Class Cutout

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mcp.cutcad.model.primitives.Cutout
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Pluggable, Drawable2D, java.io.Serializable

    public class Cutout
extends java.lang.Object
implements Drawable2D, java.io.Serializable, Pluggable
    Connects two shapes such that the second one forms a cut-out in the first one

    • Constructor Detail

      • Cutout

        public Cutout(GShape master,
      GShape slave)
        Creates a new Cut-out object, where both shapes are stored and a new position and angle is created for the positioning of the cut-out form on the master shape. The material of the cut-out shape is set to Nothing (could be of course reassigned to another, if some kind of inlay is wanted)
        Parameters:
        master - The shape, where a cut-out should appear
        slave - The shape, which is used as a cut-out form
